1. College Domain

Problem: Student Performance Prediction

Description: Predict students’ academic performance to identify those needing extra support.

Input: Attendance %, past grades, participation in activities, assignment scores, study hours.

Output: Predicted final grade (A/B/C/D/F) or risk category (High/Medium/Low).

Problem: Course Recommendation System

Description: Recommend courses to students based on their interests and past performance.

Input: Past courses taken, grades, student interests, skills, feedback ratings.

Output: Top 3–5 recommended courses for the student.


2. Healthcare Domain

Problem: Disease Prediction

Description: Predict the likelihood of a patient having a specific disease.

Input: Age, gender, medical history, lifestyle factors, lab test results, symptoms.

Output: Probability of disease (e.g., diabetes risk 0–1) or disease classification.

Problem: Medical Image Diagnosis

Description: Identify abnormalities in X-rays or MRI scans.

Input: Medical images (X-ray, CT, MRI).

Output: Detection of disease/condition (e.g., pneumonia: yes/no, tumor: benign/malignant).

Problem: Hospital Readmission Prediction

Description: Predict whether a patient is likely to be readmitted within 30 days.

Input: Patient demographics, previous hospital visits, diagnosis, treatment history.

Output: Readmission probability (High/Medium/Low).


3. Shopping / E-commerce Domain

Problem: Customer Purchase Prediction

Description: Predict what products a customer is likely to buy next.

Input: Past purchase history, browsing behavior, cart items, demographic info.

Output: Recommended products for the customer.

Problem: Customer Sentiment Analysis

Description: Analyze reviews to determine customer satisfaction.

Input: Text reviews from customers, ratings, timestamps.

Output: Sentiment classification (Positive / Negative / Neutral) or sentiment score.

Problem: Dynamic Pricing System

Description: Predict optimal pricing for products based on demand and trends.

Input: Product category, competitor pricing, seasonality, stock levels, demand history.

Output: Recommended price for the product.